record_data.record_plain_text: BEACOM ENERGY, INC. FERC ELECTRIC MBR TARIFF, VOLUME NO. 1 1. Availability: Beacom Energy, Inc. (“Seller”) makes sales of electric energy, capacity, and ancillary services available at wholesale under this market-based rate tariff (“Tariff”). 2. Applicability: This Tariff is applicable to all sales of electric energy and electric capacity by Seller that are (a) subject to the jurisdiction of the Commission, and (b) not otherwise subject to a particular rate schedule of Seller on file with the Commission. 3. Seller Category: As defined in 18 C.F.R. § 35.36(a), Seller is Category 1 in all regions. 4. Rates: All sales shall be made at rates established between the purchaser and Seller. 5. Modifications: Seller may unilaterally apply, under Federal Power Act Section 205 and the regulations promulgated thereunder, to the Commission or other regulatory agency having jurisdiction for a modification of this Tariff. 6. Ancillary Services. (a) PJM: Seller offers regulation and frequency response service, energy imbalance service, and operating reserve service (which includes spinning, 10-minute, and 30-minute reserves) for sale into the market administered by PJM Interconnection, L.L.C. (“PJM”) and, where the PJM Open Access Transmission Tariff permits, the self-supply of these services to purchasers for a bilateral sale that is used to satisfy the ancillary services requirements of the PJM Office of Interconnection; (b) MISO: Seller offers regulation and frequency response service, energy imbalance service, and operating reserve service (which includes spinning, 10-minute, and 30-minute reserves) for sale into the market administered by Midwest Independent Transmission System Operator, Inc. (“MISO”) and, where the MISO Open Access Transmission Tariff permits, the self-supply of these services to purchasers for a bilateral sale that is used to satisfy the ancillary services requirements of MISO; (c) Third-Party Provider: Seller offers Regulation Service, Energy Imbalance Service, Spinning Reserves, and Supplemental Reserves. Sales will not include the following: (1) sales to a regional transmission organization (“RTO”) or an independent system operator (“ISO”), i.e., where that entity has no ability to self-supply ancillary services but instead depends on third parties; (2) sales to a traditional, franchised public utility affiliated with Seller, or sales where the underlying transmission service is on the system of any public utility affiliated with Seller; and (3) sales to a public utility that is purchasing ancillary services to satisfy its own open access transmission tariff requirements to offer ancillary services to its own customers. 7. Limitations and Exemptions Regarding Market-Based Rate Authority: Seller has been granted waiver of Subparts B and C of Part 35 of the Commission’s regulations requiring the filing of cost-of-service information, except as to sections 35.12(a), 35.13(b), 35.15, and 35.16; granted waiver of Parts 41, 101 and 141, except for Sections 141.14 and 141.15, of the Commission’s accounting and periodic reporting regulations; and granted blanket authorization for all future issuances of securities or assumptions of liabilities pursuant to Section 204 of the Federal Power Act, 16 U.S.C. § 824e, and Part 34 of the Commission’s regulations. See Beacom Energy, Inc., Docket No. ER13-217-000. 8. Compliance with Commission Regulations: Seller shall comply with the provisions of 18 C.F.R. Part 35, Subpart H, as applicable, and with any conditions the Commission imposes in its orders concerning seller’s market-based rate authority, including orders in which the Commission authorizes seller to engage in affiliate sales under this Tariff or otherwise restricts or limits the seller’s market-based rate authority. Failure to comply with the applicable provisions of 18 C.F.R. Part 35, Subpart H, and with any orders of the Commission concerning seller’s market-based rate authority, will constitute a violation of this Tariff. 9. Other Terms and Conditions: All other terms and conditions shall be established by agreement between the purchaser and Seller. 10. Effective Date: This Tariff is effective on and after the date specified by the Commission.
